  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (bounded-envelope clean package)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The ContextOfUse declares an explicit operating envelope (flow 2–6 L/min, speed 2000–3500 RPM, hematocrit 30–45%) and an applicability constraint (adult patients, non-pulsatile CPB mode only). Validation activities densely cover this envelope across 15 experimental operating points.",
