      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison of CFD-predicted NIH against experimental measurements at all 15 validation points. Maximum relative error: 13.2% (point 7, 3.5L/2700RPM). Mean absolute relative error: 7.4%. All points within ±15% acceptance criterion for nominal points and ±18% for off-nominal points. Pressure head comparison: max error 7.3%, mean 3.8%. Validation metric (Erel) computed per ASME V&V 20-2009. Uncertainty-normalized validation metric confirms model adequacy within declared envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is NIH (mg/100L), which is the clinically accepted metric for pump-induced hemolysis and the quantity used in the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate). NIH is computed from the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model integrated along Lagrangian particle tracks. Secondary QoI (pressure head ΔP) directly supports pump performance characterization. Both QoIs are directly linked to the decision criterion and are measurable in both simulation and experiment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Validation activities conducted on the identical FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry as the COU model. Operating conditions span the full declared envelope with 15 points (5 nominal + 10 off-nominal), providing dense coverage. Experimental fluid (porcine blood, Hct 33%) is representative of clinical CPB conditions within the declared hematocrit constraint (30–45%). Non-pulsatile flow condition matches the applicability constraint. Validation dataset is independent of model calibration data. The validation domain is fully contained within and densely samples the declared operating envelope, supporting the bounded-applicability claim."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
